Bring a pan of slightly salted water plus 1 teaspoon of olive oil to a boil. Add the penne and cook until al dente, about 10 to 12 minutes. Drain and return to the pan. Mix in 1 teaspoon of olive oil. Heat 2 teaspoons of olive oil in a pan over high heat. Add the onions and saut√© until translucent. Add the bell peppers, garlic, and cook for 2 minutes, mixing occasionally. Add the broccoli, sun-dried tomatoes, red pepper flakes, and continue to cook until the vegetables are tender. Add a little bit of the sun-dried tomatoes oil, the pine nuts, basil, and season to taste. Blend in the cooked pasta and serve immediately.